node.text:
Behind every great athlete is a coach who helps them reach their potential. 

Meet Patrick Sang, coach to Eliud Kipchoge and Geoffrey Kamworor, who believes that helping athletes become better human beings is just as important as the physical work of training. Since he started coaching in 1995, Patrick has seen many of his athletes win titles and break world records. He also stood at the finish line as Eliud broke the two-hour marathon barrier last October, and since that day, the two have been preparing for Eliud to break his World Record in London.

Watch the film to learn more about the guiding philosophies of this legendary coach.

node.title: More than a Coach: Patrick Sang

node.text:
For two weeks, Blue Ribbon Sports and BRS Manager, @jjeffersoniv. traveled across the US to meet and learn from runners coast to coast. With sound advice from Nike’s First Employee, Jeff Johnson, we met runners face-to-face in their communities of Los Angeles, Chicago, and New York City. We learned from them, celebrated running, and sold exclusive BRS footwear along the way.
⠀
Throughout the tour, we met amazing runners with inspiring stories about why they started running, the importance of their respective community and the power of the run. Since our early beginnings, we’ve always known that the best way to serve the runner is face-to-face, and with Blue Ribbon Sports we’ve set out to do just that.
⠀
Watch the film and let us know where in the world you want to see BRS pop-up next.  #blueribbonsports @vw

node.text:
For Breauna and Keauna Cobb, twin sisters who came to live with @shalaneflanagan in 2016, running is all about finding your own pace and doing it when and how you want. 

“When you’re going fast there's no judgment of who you are. You're just able to be free,” says Breauna. “You have your own fast - it’s not about what other people think. Just go your own way,” adds Keauna.

Take the excitement you felt at the finish line yesterday and let it motivate you today. Maybe that means a recovery run, stretching, or an intentional day off. Maybe that means going even faster or farther today. Listen to your body!

…And discover so much more. 

When you bring another person into your routine, you aren’t just signing up for some light competition and occasional trash talk. A running partner can actually help you improve by adding accountability. 

“If you go on a 5K with someone, you’re doing all 5K. You’re with them,” says Nike Run Club Head Coach, @coachbennett. “I think that’s where the bonds become very strong in our sport.”

Find Your Drive. Find Your Fast.

@grantfisher_ goes hard, but he doesn’t go alone. He looks to his teammates on the tight knit Bowerman Track Club to take it to the next level on a daily basis.

node.text:
...It’s fun! 🎉

Forget splits, mileage counts, and stride length for a second. When you’re moving, really moving... running just feels good.

Meet our fastest family of shoes for everyday runs, training, and racing. While each excels in unique ways, they share a common thread of innovation designed to help you achieve your best.
 
Now available for members in select geographies. Hit the link in bio for more.
